{
  "stem": "21731.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I did the-- a course for-- that was a children clinic, for children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now I come back to Lvov, where I arrived not knowing anything about this world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [DRINKS] --greeted and very welcomed by my aunt, which I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were two children also, and got again sucked into the social life of a kind of small town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because Vienna was a big town, and Lvov was just a small town where everybody knew everybody.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the family of the Bernsteins and Parnuses, and now, of my future husband, Schutz, were known to everybody.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I called it the Jewish aristocracy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were all extremely rich, or wealthy, perhaps-- doctors, lawyers, dentists, accountants, bankers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The bank which I, naturally, remember most was the Bank of Schutz and Hyas, which belonged to my mother-in-law and her brother, Victor Hyas.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a very beautiful-- well, for me, a very unusual flat, with my uncle having hundreds and hundreds of books, and also gramophone records.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because he was very-- also very musical, and he loved music.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had-- I never saw so many books in my life-- I think, even later, not perhaps in one of those big houses here in England, which you visit.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that was his home, and it-- there were-- that was his room.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The-- as I said before, I was, at once, sucked into this social life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was invited everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I met Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maximilian Schutz at bridge-- not that I played, but my aunt was a great bridge player-- and he took, at once, great interest in me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Naturally, my aunt had to give her permission when he took me out to a restaurant or to the-- to a coffee bar.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
